Cybersecurity Threat Landscape (Part 2 - Akamai)
In this part, you should primarily use the Akamai_Security_Year_in_Review_2019 and Akamai State of the Internet/ Security plus independent research to answer the below questions.
______________________________________________________________________
DDOS attack events from January 2019 to September 2019 largely targeted which industry?
The gaming industry was largely targetted by DDOS Attack Events during this period & for Unique Targets the Financials Services Industry was the leader in its respective category.



Almost 50% of unique targets for DDoS attacks from January 2019- September 2019 largely targeted which industry?
The financial services sector was largely affected by phishing domains. 



Which companies are the top phishing targets, according to Akamai?
High technology industry is the top for being targeted by phishing attacks. 



What is credential stuffing?
The act of securing username & passwords without consent in order to fraudulently gain access to user accounts. 



Which country is the number one source of credential abuse attacks? Which country is number 2?
The United States takes the number one spot with Russia coming in second. 



Which country is the number one source of web application attacks? Which country is number 2?
The United States takes the number one spot with Russia coming in second. 



In Akamai’s State of the Internet report, it refers to a possible DDoS team that the company thought was affecting a customer in Asia (starts on page 11).
-   	Describe what was happening. 
An influx of web traffic overflowing the database Akamai uses to log such activity.  
-   	What did the team believe the source of the attack was?
A major DDoS attack was the original source of the attack when flagged.
-   	What did the team actually discover?
It wasn’t an attack after all, instead a warranty tool went haywire.

What is an example of a performance issue with bot traffic?
Often when bot traffic is overwhelming a server it leads to performance issues which can lead to overloading or crashing a server.



Known-good bots are bots that perform useful or helpful tasks, and not do anything malicious to sites or servers. What are the main categories of known-good bots. 
Search Engine Crawlers, Web Archives, SEO, Site Monitoring Services & Content Aggregators are all examples of good bots.


What are two evasion techniques that malicious bots use?
They will alter the User Agent, or other HTTP header values, allowing the bot to impersonate widely used browsers, mobile applications, or even known-good bots.
